<%- include('./layouts/header') %>

<main>
  <h1 class="title">Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</h1>
  
  <section class="roles-section">
    <h2>Role Features</h2>
    <div class="role-cards">
      <% if (!user) { %>
        <div class="role-card">
          <h3>Admin</h3>
          <p>Admins have full control over the system, including managing users, roles, and permissions.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Manage user accounts.</li>
            <li>Assign and update roles.</li>
            <li>Access all routes and data.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="role-card">
          <h3>Moderator</h3>
          <p>Moderators oversee specific sections and ensure the system runs smoothly.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Moderate content or users.</li>
            <li>Access routes restricted to moderators and clients.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="role-card">
          <h3>Client</h3>
          <p>Clients are end-users with limited access to services and personal content.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>View and manage their own data.</li>
            <li>Limited access to public and private routes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      <% } else if (user.role === 'ADMIN') { %>
        <div class="role-card">
          <h3>Admin</h3>
          <p>Admins have full control over the system, including managing users, roles, and permissions.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Manage user accounts.</li>
            <li>Assign and update roles.</li>
            <li>Access all routes and data.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      <% } else if (user.role === 'MODERATOR') { %>
        
        <div class="role-card">
          <h3>Moderator</h3>
          <p>Moderators oversee specific sections and ensure the system runs smoothly.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Moderate content or users.</li>
            <li>Access routes restricted to moderators and clients.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      <% } else if (user.role === 'CLIENT') { %>
        <div class="role-card">
          <h3>Client</h3>
          <p>Clients are end-users with limited access to services and personal content.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>View and manage their own data.</li>
            <li>Limited access to public and private routes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="tutorial-info">
    <h2>About the Project</h2>
    <p>
      This project demonstrates the implementation of a robust Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) system. It includes the following features:
    </p>
    <ul class="tutorial-info">
      <li><b>Express.js:</b> Backend framework for building APIs.</li>
      <li><b>EJS:</b> Templating engine for dynamic web pages.</li>
      <li><b>CSS Styling:</b> Custom CSS with responsive design for all screen sizes.</li>
      <li><b>Passport.js:</b> Local authentication (email & password).</li>
      <li><b>Role Management:</b> Admin, Moderator, and Client roles.</li>
      <li><b>Authorization:</b> Routes secured by user roles.</li>
      <li><b>Mongoose:</b> Database modeling with MongoDB.</li>
      <li><b>Express Sessions:</b> Persistent login with Mongo Store.</li>
      <li><b>Server-Side Validation:</b> Ensures data integrity.</li>
      <li><b>Flash Messages:</b> For user feedback (e.g., login success, errors).</li>
      <li><b>Custom Error Handling:</b> Handling HTTP errors like 404.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>



